  18.4.11 ESMF_CplCompIsPetLocal - Inquire if this CplComp is to execute on the
  calling PET

   INTERFACE:
   recursive function ESMF_CplCompIsPetLocal(cplcomp, rc)

   RETURN VALUE:
     logical :: ESMF_CplCompIsPetLocal

   ARGUMENTS:
     type(ESMF_CplComp), intent(in)            :: cplcomp
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
     integer,            intent(out), optional :: rc

   STATUS:
     * This interface is backward compatible with ESMF versions starting
       at 5.2.0r. If code using this interface compiles with any version
       of ESMF starting with 5.2.0r, then it will compile with the current
       version.

   DESCRIPTION:

   Inquire if this ESMF_CplComp object is to execute on the calling PET.

   The return value is .true. if the component is to execute on the
   calling PET, .false. otherwise.

   The arguments are:

   cplcomp
          ESMF_CplComp queried.

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

